The function takes four arguments:

* `Address`: The starting address of the memory range to search.
* `Size`: The size of the memory range to search.
* `Pattern`: The pattern of byte sequences to search for.
* `PatternSize`: The size of the pattern of byte sequences to search for.

The function iterates over the memory range, comparing each byte to the corresponding byte in the pattern. If all bytes match, the function returns the starting address of the matching pattern. If any byte does not match, the function continues to the next byte in the memory range.

If the function does not find a matching pattern, it returns 0.

